Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.51,0:01:49.81,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.67,0:01:52.23,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:53.38,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}And the parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:56.17,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I got them here in one piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.85,0:01:59.17,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,They're there if we look for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.59,0:02:03.02,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:05.85,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.90,0:02:08.14,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.14,0:02:11.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it your turn to clean the yard today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:14.77,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I had something I wanted to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.77,0:02:15.74,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:31.25,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been half a year since Kanata came to this fortress, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.05,0:02:34.20,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She plays well now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:36.63,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because she has a good teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.63,0:02:37.40,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:45.89,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems I won't be needing my earplugs anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:50.69,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:54.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a better idea to stay in town this winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:02:56.96,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:03:01.16,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't die that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.01,0:03:09.16,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been living alone on this mountain for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:17.00,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Steady, steady...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:19.92,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Steady... Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:23.34,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally coming together, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.34,0:03:25.35,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you handle the rest, Noel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:28.14,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm happy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.71,0:03:31.36,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have some tea, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.36,0:03:31.97,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.30,0:03:40.66,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kureha-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.95,0:03:44.62,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.62,0:03:46.04,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:48.73,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's supposed to be here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.37,0:03:52.61,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:55.48,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where we keep the army's roster, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:59.36,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata said she wanted to know about Her Highness Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:03.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.44,0:04:05.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's not there, I don't know where it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.72,0:04:07.14,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Bummer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:10.24,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Naomi-san might have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.80,0:04:12.74,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask her next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.74,0:04:13.43,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:29.20,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness Princess Iliya is the eldest daughter of the current Arkadian Archduke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.15,0:04:32.45,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've told you about this before,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:36.25,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,but anyway, she was a very famous tanker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:40.06,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Claus-san said, "if only she was alive," the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:42.78,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:44.37,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:45.98,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,About two years ago, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.50,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,In the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:49.05,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.39,0:04:54.50,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness was assigned to the Royal Guard division,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.50,0:04:59.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,but they also put her in charge of boosting national morale,\Nso she traveled around the country a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:02.52,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, as she was returning from a certain town,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:05.83,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,she tried to save a child who was drowning in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:12.12,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I'm a bit glad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.48,0:05:16.08,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a rumor, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.55,0:05:21.83,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:23.93,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.50,0:05:26.64,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.47,0:05:28.64,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,and, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:41.77,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.27,0:05:44.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.62,0:05:46.72,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.66,0:05:49.70,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She brought Yuuko-chan with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:54.46,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Yuuko-chan is Martin-san's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.21,0:05:58.63,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, um, old lady Jacott was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.63,0:06:02.52,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Jacott-san is an old lady living alone in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:05.49,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I sometimes buy vegetables from her at the morning market...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.49,0:06:09.72,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you said the pickles the other day were delicious, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.29,0:06:13.39,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was the one who grew them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:19.73,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,And, um... Jacott-san hasn't been around lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.61,0:06:24.71,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a weak body, so they're worried about her...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:29.00,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She seems to live deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.00,0:06:29.81,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,And, um{\fscx300}-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:32.20,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, alright already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.25,0:06:35.93,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hear you out. Wait a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:38.37,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:45.84,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to improve our relations with the holy city of Rome, Her Highness Princess Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:49.47,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,was to be wed to the emperor.\NThat's what people were saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:52.47,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But that would've made her his third Empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:54.99,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The third! His third one, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:56.72,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.86,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd be nothing but a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:05.23,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But then Her Highness passed away, and it all stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:10.35,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we were still at war until the armistice this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:14.53,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.11,0:07:16.75,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:20.25,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,An unfinished house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.92,0:07:24.34,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say she lives by herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.34,0:07:26.00,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.93,0:07:36.89,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.87,0:07:39.89,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.28,0:07:42.14,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yuuko sent you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:42.88,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.87,0:07:45.74,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a sweet girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.87,0:07:50.78,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She's too good to be that bratty Martin's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.37,0:07:53.40,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a pretty house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.83,0:07:55.06,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.89,0:07:59.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I built this house myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.19,0:08:00.89,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.89,0:08:01.41,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.88,0:08:04.66,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,What about that house over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.66,0:08:08.21,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That house is for my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.21,0:08:10.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:14.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,He lives in a faraway town right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.09,0:08:17.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm preparing it so he can come home anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:23.81,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,My son and he might have use for it at any given time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.35,0:08:27.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,so I need to prepare it properly for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.94,0:08:43.20,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,When will that son of yours be back, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:45.46,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.46,0:08:47.78,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Winter will be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.28,0:08:51.65,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You should get off the mountain before the snow arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.65,0:08:53.46,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That I cannot do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:09:01.08,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I must complete that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:05.55,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't leave this place before it's done,\Neven if it costs me my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.55,0:09:05.95,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But{\fscx300}-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.95,0:09:07.94,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop this nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.94,0:09:10.27,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,How are your preparations for winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.27,0:09:12.49,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are your firewood and food stocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.49,0:09:14.45,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't prepared any of it, have you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.89,0:09:18.28,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get through it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:22.45,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for worrying about me, both of you girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.33,0:09:24.87,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.90,0:09:34.84,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, she's a hardheaded old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.46,0:09:39.41,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the both of you are similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.41,0:09:41.10,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.10,0:09:42.61,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,How am I{\fscx300}-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.61,0:09:47.35,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sometimes, you aren't honest with yourself as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:48.61,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.71,0:09:52.76,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, about that letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.48,0:09:56.09,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,why did you show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.62,0:10:02.33,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I was informed in last week's scheduled communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.33,0:10:07.75,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,that the Roman armies along the eastern border\Nhave started to mobilize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:33.07,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:34.98,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}It's for old lady Jacott?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:37.49,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}Alright then, take these too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:39.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.57,0:10:40.91,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:44.62,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,700)}do you know anything about the peace conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:46.60,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.60,0:10:47.87,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.87,0:10:50.55,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,If only Princess Iliya was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.55,0:10:52.41,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, Martin,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.45,0:10:56.62,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't Princess Iliya have a little sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.31,0:10:58.65,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Your change, four million yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.65,0:10:59.92,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Hadn't heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:03.60,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's the Archduke and his mistress's daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:05.64,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,so she wasn't talked about much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.19,0:11:09.52,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the third in line for the throne or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:12.38,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, about her sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.34,0:11:21.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.19,0:11:22.06,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.77,0:11:24.82,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:30.84,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we take a walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.95,0:11:33.83,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:37.96,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place is your hometown?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.11,0:11:41.84,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a typical country town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.27,0:11:46.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,We have fields, and lots of cattle and goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.19,0:11:48.45,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But there aren't many people there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.46,0:11:51.85,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it feels a bit different from this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.59,0:11:54.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a nice place, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.05,0:11:57.82,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet your parents were nice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:11:59.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.00,0:12:03.70,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of environment were you raised in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.75,0:12:12.46,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I was raised in a place away from the government complex,\Nwith a beautiful forest and lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.62,0:12:14.99,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a small town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.53,0:12:20.22,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I lived there with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.02,0:12:25.43,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The days we spent were boring,\Nand nothing special would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:33.11,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The only comfort I looked forward to was my loving sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.18,0:12:38.98,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,We had different mothers, but she sometimes came to visit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.98,0:12:41.53,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was someone I looked up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:47.67,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was so dignified and kind,\Naccepting her destiny as a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.36,0:12:52.25,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was the one who taught me the trumpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:55.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, she was too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.47,0:12:59.59,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was too kind, and because of it, she lost her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.79,0:13:05.63,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I only thought this town was simply inconvenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.25,0:13:13.72,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I got lost and ended up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.72,0:13:16.89,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,and I thought I had finally reached my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.28,0:13:21.90,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, later I realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.96,0:13:26.11,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This was just another dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.58,0:13:29.95,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.81,0:13:35.02,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose my way quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.02,0:13:38.15,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I like getting lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.37,0:13:42.50,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing wrong with getting lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:44.39,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Or reaching a dead end!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:51.10,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Since, because of that, I met you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.68,0:14:01.48,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I really envy you sometimes, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:10.75,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I was as honest with myself as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.19,0:14:31.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.19,0:14:34.70,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you care so much about someone like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.20,0:14:40.22,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You remind me of my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.09,0:14:45.23,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember giving birth to someone as pretty as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.22,0:14:49.90,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born from a forbidden love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:51.24,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was always waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:56.11,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Each year, she would wait for him,\Nwithout knowing if he was coming or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.11,0:15:01.25,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She died living an unfulfilled life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:06.80,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you decide it was unfulfilled?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:08.04,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's{\fscx300}-{\fscx100}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:10.03,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:16.31,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, he promised me he'd come back someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:19.64,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd come take me away someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.64,0:15:22.01,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy with just that promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:23.06,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, that's{\fscx300}-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:28.20,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,What else do you think I could do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:29.59,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.59,0:15:33.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,If there {\i1}was{\i0} something I could do, I might have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.07,0:15:35.18,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.17,0:15:38.34,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really okay like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:40.21,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you truly feel happy with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.14,0:15:44.29,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I have memories of my love for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.00,0:15:47.27,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I have memories of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:50.63,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I have hope that I can meet him again someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.38,0:15:55.18,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,That's more than enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:09.32,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a feeling it'd snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.29,0:16:33.27,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The first time I met you, it was a snowy day like today, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.59,0:16:47.31,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when Madam was still young,\NSeize was prospering as a resort town.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.94,0:17:09.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell in love with a young merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:19.14,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Soon afterwards, she gave birth to his child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.50,0:17:23.51,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he already had a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.14,0:17:29.30,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a blessing for him,\Nsince his legal wife couldn't bear a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.30,0:17:34.37,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,He took their child and returned to his hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.54,0:17:42.04,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,He promised her he'd come back someday and take her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:10.28,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:12.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.71,0:18:12.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,At this age, I think back at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.81,0:18:15.98,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,"What if, back then..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:20.28,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Jacott-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.69,0:18:23.83,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, life consists of losing something again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:27.48,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But you must gain something first, before you can lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.48,0:18:34.03,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The greater the happiness gained,\Nthe greater the suffering when lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.09,0:18:43.78,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But, as long as we have memories of that happiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.06,0:18:48.81,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because of those memories that we can continue living.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:56.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.44,0:19:01.41,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this isn't the best time,\Nbut I found Princess Iliya's picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.41,0:19:02.28,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.01,0:19:05.16,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Filicia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.88,0:19:10.79,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was about five years ago when the Princess visited Seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.13,0:19:16.44,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this Shuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:29.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.66,0:20:27.83,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, my parents wanted to marry me off,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.72,0:20:32.43,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,so that someone could inherit the family business.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.13,0:20:38.75,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, I heard that trumpet's melody.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.11,0:20:42.19,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forget it, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.35,0:20:44.70,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.64,0:20:47.49,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya-san, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.17,0:20:52.60,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've met her too, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.59,0:20:55.21,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.86,0:20:58.65,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya-san's note resounds within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.20,0:21:02.51,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, we met each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.10,0:21:10.04,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I was running away by coming to this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.45,0:21:13.40,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,so I didn't think about it too much in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.80,0:21:17.80,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that I'd leave this town eventually anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.89,0:21:23.97,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I honestly don't want to leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.80,0:21:28.87,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's why I must go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.23,0:21:31.55,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.95,0:21:35.52,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, there's something only I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.39,0:21:43.56,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.87,0:21:50.16,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Because no matter how far apart we are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:54.21,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The note will resound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.21,0:21:56.43,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,The note will resound, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.07,0:22:01.21,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,It will connect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:07.96,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, was I a good senior to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.75,0:22:11.71,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.67,0:22:31.53,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, that's how Senpai came to leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.15,0:22:42.51,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,She left behind a very beautiful sound of the sky\Nthat will resound in my heart, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.24,0:24:20.05,SoraNoWoto,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Next episode: A Visitor - A Burning Field of Snow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.85,0:00:18.24,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}The radiance of this sky will carry to your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:28.55,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}The melody you dreamed of is like serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.55,0:00:33.54,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}For your hands the dream is still far away, but
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.54,0:00:38.54,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}remember the voice so gentle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.55,0:00:51.23,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}when someone sang the chord of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:01:00.70,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}The sound of the skies echoes high over all sadness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.70,0:01:11.34,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}Everything reflected in your eyes is the real world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.34,0:01:20.68,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}Not even the shedding of of tears can stop you here
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.68,0:01:33.24,OP-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2.2\fad(130,130)}We're playing tomorrow in the light that rains without end
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.23,0:22:51.02,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Resonate the feelings of love and friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.02,0:22:54.11,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Let's perform the important things
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.50,0:23:12.11,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}I cried when I was happy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.25,0:23:18.06,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}I laughed when I was hurt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.52,0:23:27.37,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}But, they're all proof that I'm alive
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.37,0:23:31.51,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Let's walk slowly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:33.36,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Everybody singing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.36,0:23:37.46,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Tell me what you truly want
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.46,0:23:38.73,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}You're just my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:44.89,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Even if love and friendship change over time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.94,0:23:44.89,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2\an1\3c&H5ECC69&}I know, You know little happy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.89,0:23:50.35,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}I want them to echo forever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.89,0:23:50.89,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2\an1\3c&H5ECC69&}Can you hear my precious note?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.89,0:23:56.67,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}Speaking endless words touched by love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.67,0:24:02.81,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}This is our harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.83,0:24:07.44,ED-TL,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,150)\blur2}I can hear our harmony
